io.github.goodees.ese.core.sync

Class ProxiedSyncEventSourcingRuntime<E extends ProxiedSyncEntity<R>,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.goodees.ese.core.sync.ProxiedSyncEventSourcingRuntime<E,R>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProxiedSyncEventSourcingRuntime.WithAsyncInterface

    public abstract class ProxiedSyncEventSourcingRuntime<E extends ProxiedSyncEntity<R>,R>
extends Object
    Runtime for proxied sync entities. This offers the simplest interface for invoking methods on entities, but has few drawbacks. The actual invocation is still asynchronous, going over Dispatcher, therefore multiple execute methods exists, that define how the result should be fetched from the completable future.
    See Also:
    ProxiedSyncEntity

      • getScheduler

        protected abstract ScheduledExecutorService getScheduler()

        Returns:

      • retryDelay

        protected long retryDelay(String id,
                          String methodName,
                          Throwable error,
                          int attempts)
        Specify whether and when the request should be retried in case of failure. Should return redelivery delay in milliseconds. Returning 0 means to retry immediately, returning less than 0 means not to retry.

        If retry is greater than zero, the runtime may execute other requests before the wait period expires

        Parameters:
        id - identity of the entity
        methodName - name of the method that failed
        error - the throwable the request failed with
        attempts - number of attempts for execution of that request. Greater than 1.
        Returns:
        negative for failing the request, zero for immediate retry, positive for delay in ms until next attempt
        See Also:
        for exactly the same information
